The paper discusses the validation of a deep learning system for the automated detection of diabetic retinopathy and age-related macular degeneration in color fundus images. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. The use of deep learning algorithms for medical image analysis also relates to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential for the system to become a reliable support for ophthalmological experts, which relates to the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of the system for medical purposes, which relates to the medical imaging (cs.MED) category.
